  "body": "If you take a look at the API of a component, you get things like:\n\n`render`\n`props`\n`getInitialState`\n\nAnd that's fine.\n\nHowever, lifecycle methods are all named like if the component was talking about itself using the third person:\n\n`componentWillMount`\n`shouldComponentUpdate`\n\nCan't we use normal method names here too? (`willMount`, `shouldUpdate`) We will gain space and consistency.\n",
